<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>HTTP/3 AND QUIC SECURITY</title>

  <critical>HTTP/3 built on QUIC introduces new attack surfaces including UDP-based amplification, connection migration hijacking, and 0-RTT replay attacks. Many security tools don't properly inspect QUIC traffic, creating blind spots for defenders and opportunities for attackers.</critical>

  <scope>
    - QUIC protocol vulnerabilities
    - 0-RTT replay attacks
    - Connection migration hijacking
    - UDP amplification attacks
    - Certificate handling differences
    - Middlebox and WAF bypass
  </scope>

  <methodology>
    1. QUIC DETECTION AND ENUMERATION
       {% raw %}
       # Check for HTTP/3 support
       curl -I --http3 https://target.com

       # Using h3spec for QUIC testing
       h3spec https://target.com

       # Check Alt-Svc header for QUIC advertisement
       curl -I https://target.com | grep -i alt-svc

       # Wireshark QUIC filter
       quic

       # Using quiche for QUIC connections
       cargo run --example client https://target.com
       {% endraw %}

    2. 0-RTT REPLAY ATTACKS
